## Image pipeline — how to re-run or extend

To fetch images for any remaining null fragrances (e.g. after adding new fragrances to the DB):
```bash
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=<service_role_key> \
  npx ts-node --compiler-options '{"module":"CommonJS"}' \
  scripts/fetch-fragrance-images.ts
```
Processes only fragrances where `imageUrl IS NULL`. Options: `--dry-run`, `--limit N`, `--slug S`, `--force` (reprocess all, overwriting existing).

To fix a specific fragrance after manually identifying its correct Fragrantica ID:
```bash
# Set imageUrl directly in DB, e.g.:
# fimgs.net/mdimg/perfume/375x500.{fragrantica_id}.jpg → download + upload to Supabase
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=<service_role_key> \
  npx ts-node --compiler-options '{"module":"CommonJS"}' \
  scripts/fetch-fragrance-images.ts --slug <slug> --force
```

## Design constants (carry forward)

- Background: `#0c0906` · Body: `stone-200` · Accent: `amber-500`/`amber-400`
- Labels: `text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em]` · Card border: `border-stone-800`, hover `border-stone-600`
